validations.message: Only numbers, capital letters and dashes "-" are allowed.

settings.helpText: Describes your image for anyone who can't see it. This includes: search engines and people using screen-readers. If you leave this blank, the image title will be used for alt text.
Optional, but recommended if you are creating an Article Vine.
Briefly summarise the main topic or contention of the article. Used primarily for SEO and social media sharing, but may also be used for content previews and other summary components.
Auto generated based on your title. Helps with SEO-friendly urls.
99.9% of the time, this will be "Link"
99.99% of the time this will be a URL.
The visible text part that users will click on.
Used for title or aria-label attributes to give additional information and context to people with screenreaders. Also helpful for SEO.
Describes your image for anyone who can't see it. This includes: search engines and people using screen-readers. If you leave this blank, the image title will be used for alt text.
The person's given and family names, in preferred order (eg English names use "GivenName FamilyName", while Japanese names are written as "FamilyName GivenName").
The preferred name to use when referring to this person. Usually this will just be their given name.
The date this person joined the Royals.
Unique identifier use for URLs and SEO. Will usually be autogenerated when you first add a title.
Optional field. If the group has specific leader(s), add them here rather in the general Members collection.
